title: Gavin Newsom
deleted: In November 2020, Newsom attended a birthday dinner for one of his political advisors, which he was criticized for given the raging [[COVID-19 pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]]. Newsom later apologized for his actions.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Korte|first=Lara|date= November 13, 2020|title=Gavin Newsom catches heat for attending birthday party as he urges COVID-19 restrictions|work=Sacramento Bee|url=https://www.sacbee.com/news/politics-government/capitol-alert/article247175656.html#storylink=cpy|url-status=live|access-date=}}</ref>

title: Gavin Newsom
deleted: On October 3, 2020, a Tweet from the Office of the Governor of California contained two contradictory messages: one stated in writing that anyone going out to eat should "keep your mask on in between bites" and the other message was an image with the message to "Minimize the number of times you take your mask off." <ref>{{Cite web|last=Governor of California|first=Office of the|date=|title=Office of the Governor of California on Twitter: "Going out to eat with members of your household this weekend? Don't forget to keep your mask on in between bites."|url=https://twitter.com/cagovernor/status/1312437371460173825|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201004035214/https://twitter.com/cagovernor/status/1312437371460173825|archive-date=2020-10-04|access-date=2020-11-28|website=Twitter|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Tweet From Governor's Office Says to Put Mask On In Between Bites|url=https://www.nbcsandiego.com/news/local/tweet-from-governors-office-says-to-put-mask-on-in-between-bites/2420692/|access-date=2020-11-28|website=NBC 7 San Diego|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=California governor's office tells diners to wear masks "in between bites"|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/gavin-newsom-california-face-mask-restaurant/|access-date=2020-11-28|website=www.cbsnews.com|language=en-US}}</ref>

title: Gavin Newsom
deleted: An effort to recall Governor Newsom began early 2020, led by the California Patriot Coalition, and has gathered about 800,000 petition signatures, over half of the required number needed to qualify the recall for an election. The effort has been granted an extension until March 17th, 2021 to collect a total of nearly 1,500,000 signatures.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Marinucci|first=Carla|title=French Laundry snafu reignites longshot Newsom recall drive|url=https://politi.co/3nOImia|access-date=2020-12-03|website=Politico PRO|language=en}}</ref><ref>https://recallgavin2020.com/</ref>
